00:00:15.140 --> 00:00:20.380
 Chapter One. There it is.

00:00:20.380 --> 00:00:27.300
 The year 1144 of the Age of Exiles, Hound Moon.

00:00:27.300 --> 00:00:35.580
 There it is, fell through the night air, weightless. He caught glimpses of the Tower

00:00:35.580 --> 00:00:41.540
 of Brickhan, Caledas's still smoldering outline at the window, then below, the river coming up

00:00:41.540 --> 00:00:47.940
 to meet him. He slammed into the water, the cold shocking the breath out of him. He panicked,

00:00:47.940 --> 00:00:54.300
 disorientated, realising he didn't know which way was up. All about him was darkness and ice.

00:00:54.300 --> 00:01:00.780
 Then something grabbed his hair, and he was surging upwards, breaking through the water

00:01:00.780 --> 00:01:05.860
 in a burst of spray, and saw Alcion's pale broad face staring back at him.

00:01:05.860 --> 00:01:11.460
 "They will come hunting for us," the giant shouted over the roar of the river,

00:01:11.460 --> 00:01:16.220
 as the current gripped them, sweeping them away from the thunder of warriors feet crossing the

00:01:16.220 --> 00:01:24.260
 bridge. "Let the water take us far from them." Veridos saw the sense of that, though his hands and

00:01:24.260 --> 00:01:30.100
 feet were already numbing from the cold. He put some effort into swimming, speeding his

00:01:30.100 --> 00:01:37.060
 way from Brickhan, from Caledas, from the Kadashim. The thought still jolted him like a blow.

00:01:37.060 --> 00:01:43.460
 They turned a bend in the river, and the fortress was gone, darkness enfolding them.

00:01:43.460 --> 00:01:50.420
 The soft, weak sheen of Dorn's grey light filtered down through the lattice of branches above,

00:01:50.420 --> 00:01:55.820
 as Veridos met Alcion's gaze, an unspoken agreement passing between them,

00:01:55.820 --> 00:02:01.940
 as they both headed for the riverbank. It was harder going, swimming across the current,

00:02:01.940 --> 00:02:07.780
 and Veridos realised how exhausted his body was, but eventually he felt silt beneath his feet,

00:02:07.780 --> 00:02:13.060
 his hands grasping at Reeds as he pulled himself out of the water and flopped onto his back,

00:02:13.060 --> 00:02:22.100
 gasping, his limbs feeling lead-filled. Turning, he saw Alcion on the bank, thirty of forty paces up

00:02:22.100 --> 00:02:26.860
