00:02:26.860 --> 00:02:34.980
 water dripping from his drooping moustache. "Thank you," Alcion said. "For what?"

00:02:34.980 --> 00:02:41.420
 "Everything. Most of all for helping my family escape Brickhan's dungeons."

00:02:41.420 --> 00:02:46.660
 His wife and bairn. "How long has he gone without seeing them?"

00:02:46.660 --> 00:02:52.340
 "And what must he have suffered, knowing they were Calidus and Lycus' prisoners?"

00:02:52.340 --> 00:03:01.180
 "And for destroying Calidus' effigy of me," Alcion continued. "You have set me free."

00:03:01.180 --> 00:03:10.740
 He gave a shudder, followed by a smile. "A shadow is gone from my soul. I feel reborn.

00:03:10.740 --> 00:03:17.460
 If you mean you feel weak as a newborn bairn," Veredis muttered as he emptied his boot of water

00:03:17.460 --> 00:03:20.300
 and tried to pull it back on, "then I feel the same."

00:03:20.300 --> 00:03:27.100
 "That is not what I mean," the giant rumbled, regarding Veredis with serious eyes.

00:03:27.100 --> 00:03:37.460
 "You set Reiner and Tain free. You set me free. I owe you a debt beyond all imagining."

00:03:37.460 --> 00:03:44.580
 "You're in no debt to me," Veredis said. "I kicked the effigies into the fire on impulse,

00:03:44.580 --> 00:03:48.460
 not really knowing what they were or what power they held over you."

00:03:48.460 --> 00:03:52.060
 "But you suspected?" "Aye."

00:03:52.060 --> 00:03:55.060
 "Something that Fidele said."

00:03:55.060 --> 00:04:01.140
 He thought of Nathair's mother, hoped that she had made it to freedom along with his brother,

00:04:01.140 --> 00:04:09.540
 Krellus, McKean and Albin. "And your wife and son, I set them free because it was the right thing to

00:04:09.540 --> 00:04:21.100
 do. There was no other choice." "Ah, but there was, true heart, there always is," Veredis shrugged.

00:04:21.100 --> 00:04:29.140
 "There is no debt between us. You are my friend." "One of my only friends," it has turned out.

